a) Halve the @green pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded) and chop into small pieces. b) Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). c) Trim the @mangetout{80%g} then chop in into thirds. d) Cut the @tenderstem broccoli{150%g} in half widthways. e) Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Drain and rinse the @red kidney beans{1%can} in a #sieve{}.

a) Heat a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. b) When hot, add the pepper and onion. c) Cook until soft, stirring often, ~{4-5%minutes}. d) Meanwhile, pour the boiling water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} and bring back to the boil.

a) When the veggies have softened, stir in the @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @ground cumin{2%tsp}, @tomato puree{15%g} and @easy garlic{1/2}(puréed). b) Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water to stop the spices burning.

c) Add the @steamed basmati rice{1} and kidney beans to the pan. d) Stir and cook until piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}.

a) Meanwhile, when the #saucepan{} of water is boiling, add the mange tout and tenderstem and cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}. b) Drain in a #colander{} then return to the pan off the heat. c) Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

a) In a small #bowl{}, mix the coriander with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. b) Season the rice to taste with salt and pepper. c) Get ready to serve.

a) Share the rice mixture between your bowls and top with the green beans and tenderstem. b) Finish with a sprinkling of @flaked almonds{15%g} and a drizzle of the coriander dressing. Enjoy!